Additionally, the use of LSTM and BiLSTM models, as well as pre-trained word embeddings, are common techniques in this field. 

The paper may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves the use of deep learning models for aspect extraction. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with a task that falls under the umbrella of AI, specifically natural language processing. 

cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible sub-category as aspect extraction is a task that can be useful in information retrieval systems. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the use of neural networks for aspect extraction.
